title: The Harvester
creator: Gene Stratton-Porter
description: LibriVox recording of The Harvester, by Gene Stratton-Porter. Read by Cindy Steib. The Harvester is one of Gene Stratton-Porter’s romantic novels which combine a love of nature, high moral ideals and a good plot.This is the story of a young man who lives in the country side with his dog and other animals and grows herbs to sell to medical drug supply houses. One evening, he has a vision of his Dream Girl and this is the story of his search for her and what happens when he finds her.
